### DevConnect API - CQRS Implementation Tests
### Updated endpoints with Command Query Responsibility Segregation

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5257
@token = {{login.response.body.token}}

### 1. Register a new user (Command)
# POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@devconnect.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### 2. Login user (Query)
# POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@devconnect.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### 3. Register another user for role testing
# POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@devconnect.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### 4. Get available roles (Query)
# GET {{baseUrl}}/api/user-roles/available-roles
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/user-roles/available-roles
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 5. Change user role (Command) - Admin only
# PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/user-roles/change-role
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/user-roles/change-role
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userEmail": "user@devconnect.com",
  "roleName": "Administrator"
}

### 6. Test unauthorized access (should fail without admin role)
# PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/user-roles/change-role
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/user-roles/change-role
Authorization: Bearer invalid_token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userEmail": "user@devconnect.com",
  "roleName": "User"
}

### Notes:
### - CQRS pattern implemented with separate Commands and Queries
### - Commands: RegisterUserCommand, ChangeUserRoleCommand
### - Queries: LoginUserQuery, GetAvailableRolesQuery
### - Each operation has its own dedicated handler
### - No services injected directly into endpoints
### - Clean separation of concerns following CQRS principles
